YELLOW FEVER, MONKEYS - BRAZIL (SOUTH): CORRECTION
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[This replaces an erroneous correction sent yesterday - ProMED-mail]
Date: 12 Dec 2002
Source: Miss Jo Lawrence <jlawrence@phls.org.uk>
In regards to the ProMED post of 10 Dec 2002, archive number
20021210.6032, the area of Rio Grande Do Sul for which yellow fever
vaccination is recommended is the Northwest of the state, NOT
northeast.
--
Jo Lawrence (Miss)
Travel Health Surveillance
Communicable Disease Surveillance Centre
UK
<jlawrence@phls.org.uk>
[Thanks to Miss Lawrence for the correction. I apologize for the
error made in editing the original report. - Mod.LM]
